                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14461878" author="pledbrook" created="Thu, 4 May 2006 06:08:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added a patch to MarkupBuilder and its corresponding unit test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461860" author="pledbrook" created="Thu, 4 May 2006 06:13:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch I have provided adds a few extra private methods for handling the XML escaping because I wanted to provide slightly different behaviour for escaping attribute values and element content (apostrophes only need escaping inside attribute values). However, this would have meant changing the signature of transformValue(), which I was loath to do because it has &quot;protected&quot; access and changing it may have affected clients that depend on its current behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Having said that, I did fix transformValue() so that it replaces apostrophes with the correct entity (&amp;apos;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461987" author="pledbrook" created="Mon, 12 Jun 2006 11:04:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new patch adds a small fix so that empty elements are handled correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14462023" author="galleon" created="Fri, 16 Jun 2006 05:50:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch applied and tested&lt;br/&gt;
thanks peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466434" author="svalivarthi" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2009 15:41:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you please tell me which release this issue went into?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466416" author="guillaume" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2009 17:11:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It must have been already fixed in Groovy 1.0, so that&apos;s a long time ago.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466366" author="svalivarthi" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2009 08:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am still seeing the same issue on 1.5.6 and did not see a fix version on this issue so was just clarifying.. Thanks again for the great product!!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466356" author="svalivarthi" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2009 13:18:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am sorry, Please ignore my earlier comment it does work with the latest groovy code. Thanks again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
